    <stitle>NEWAY AIR SUSPENSION - SPECIFICATIONS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>SPECIFICATIONS</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="3">
            <title>TORQUE SPECIFICATIONS</title>
            <para>See
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0300221">Figure 21</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>When tightening bushing or torque rod fasteners to specifications, the vehicle must be at
                        proper ride height to avoid introducing unnecessary stress on the bushings.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f0300221" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0300221" filename="../figg03/g0300221.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 21. TORQUE LOCATIONS AND SPECIFIED VALUE</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1.NUT, LOCK - SPECIAL "SMART NUT"</callout1>
                    <callout1>2.NUT, LOCK FLANGE HEAD 1/2-20 UNF 31 TO 38 FT-LBS. (42 TO 52 N&#8226;M)</callout1>
                    <callout1>3.NUT, LOCK HEX 3/4-16 UNF 31 TO 38 FT-LBS. (42 TO 52 N&#8226;M)</callout1>
                    <callout1>4.SHOCK MTG. (UPPER AND LOWER) 110 TO 148 FT-LBS. (150 TO 200 N&#8226;M)</callout1>
                    <callout1>5.NUT, HEX LOCK 1 1/4-12 UNF 600 TO 700 FT-LBS. (813 TO 949 N&#8226;M)</callout1>
                    <callout1>6.BOLT 1/2-13 UNC 50 TO 60 FT-LBS. (68 TO 81 N&#8226;M)</callout1>
                    <callout1>7.NUT, HEX LOCK 3/4-16 UNF 175 TO 215 FT-LBS. (238 TO 292 N&#8226;M)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0300222" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0300222" filename="../figg03/g0300222.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 22. TORQUE LOCATIONS AND SPECIFIED VALUES</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1.NUT, LOCK FLANGE HEAD 5/8-18 UNF 200 TO 240 FT-LBS. (272 TO 325 N&#8226;M)</callout1>
                    <callout1>2.NUT, HEX LOCK 1 1/8-12 200 TO 225 FT-LBS. (272 TO 306 N&#8226;M)</callout1>
                    <callout1>3.NUT, HEX LOCK 1 1/8 UNRF 550 TO 600 FT-LBS. (746 TO 813 N&#8226;M)</callout1>
                    <callout1>4.NUT, HEX LOCK 3/4-10 UNC 250 TO 300 FT-LBS. (340 TO 407 N&#8226;M)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0300223" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0300223" filename="../figg03/g0300223.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 23. RIDE HEIGHT ADJUSTMENT</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1.FRAME RAIL</callout1>
                    <callout1>2.AIR SPRING HEIGHT</callout1>
                    <callout1>3.REAR REAR AIR SPRING</callout1>
                    <callout1>4.AXLE/WHEEL CENTER</callout1>
                    <callout1>5.RIDE HEIGHT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
